@node intro "Introduction"

Clustal V is a program for carrying out the alignment of multiple DNA or
protein sequences. The program was designed to be reliable, accurate and
reasonably fast on personal computers. This Amiga version is fully compatible
with versions of Clustal V available for the Unix workstations that normally
run such software.

The program imports sequences from a variety of file formats, and produces
sequence alignments/phylogenetic tree data from the input.


This program is supplied totally free of charge, but consider it emailware,
i.e. if you like it, and find it useful, then give me a quick email (brett@
babylon6.demon.co.uk).

If enough people find it useful, then I will consider porting other molecular biology
software to the Amiga. Note that I would be especially grateful if someone lets
me know if the version of Clustal V compiled for the 68030+68882 FPU works, as
I am unable to test it. :-(


@endnode

